{"title":"All Jacked Up, the New and Improved Handlebar Jack v.3","link":"https://bikerumor.com/new-and-improved-handlebar-jack-v-3/","date":1701445589000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1080\" height=\"608\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-on-cobblestone.jpeg\" alt=\"Handlebar Jack v3 on cobblestone\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-on-cobblestone.jpeg 1080w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-on-cobblestone-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-on-cobblestone-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-on-cobblestone-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-on-cobblestone-768x432.jpeg 768w\" /></p>\n<p>Back again with a better version of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-original-handlebar-jack-makes-repairs-a-cinch-w-uber-simple-design/\">OG</a>, the new Handlebar Jack version 3 has some additional features to help make trail-side repairs easier than ever. Quite simply, the Handlebar Jack is a simple, no-nonsense way to tackle trailside repairs that won’t cost you an arm and a leg. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-in-use.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-in-use-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Handlebar Jack v3 in use\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-in-use-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-in-use-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-in-use-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-in-use-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-in-use.jpeg 1080w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Handlebar Jack)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The most common way to repair a flat tire is to flip the bike upside down. I mean, we’ve been doing this since we were kids, right? With some of the new cockpit accessories, ebike controls, computer mounts, or maybe just your <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-spurcycle-original-bicycle-bell/\">favorite bell</a>, the simple solution just got less simple. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s where this clever tool comes into play. Let’s see what version 3 offers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What’s New with v3?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Handlebar Jack v3 ribbed cradle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-ribbed-cradle.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Enhanced Grip</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>They’ve made significant changes to the cradle area, where the bar meets the Jack on the v3. Adding rubber “ribs” to that area means an enhanced grip, meaning more stability and security ensuring that your bike stays put while performing the repair or maintenance. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-thicker-straps.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-thicker-straps-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Handlebar Jack v3 thicker straps\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-thicker-straps-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-thicker-straps-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-thicker-straps-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-thicker-straps-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-thicker-straps.jpeg 1080w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Thicker Strap</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This new and improved v3 now comes with a thicker strap, adding to the durability of the Handlebar Jack, even during the toughest use. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Handlebar Jack v3 more height\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-more-height.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Increased Height</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Version 3’s taller height of a full 3.7″ of clearance is the same height as the previous version while using the optional extender. This gives you more height without carrying extra components, helping keep the bike’s cockpit vitals off the ground. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Handlebar Jack v3 Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $38.95 </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-the-set-e1700674308657.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"397\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-the-set-e1700674308657-800x397.jpeg\" alt=\"Handlebar Jack v3 the set\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-the-set-e1700674308657-800x397.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-the-set-e1700674308657-297x147.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-the-set-e1700674308657-120x60.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-the-set-e1700674308657-768x381.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Handlebar-Jack-v3-the-set-e1700674308657.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Original Handlebar jack v3 is sold as a set. Two Jacks are included in the set. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.handlebarjack.com/\">HandleBarJack.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-and-improved-handlebar-jack-v-3/\">All Jacked Up, the New and Improved Handlebar Jack v.3</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"25773da282cede041383687ad719733fd82c4d6ebc5632c68252c8bcf02b0c95","category":"Cycling"}